criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  i) being children or adolescents (6 months -18 years old);

          -  ii) to have a diagnosis of oncological or hematological disease;

          -  iii) receiving an autologous or allogeneic HSCT;

          -  iv) to have spoken and written Italian language comprehension, both by
             children/adolescents and by parents.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  i) to be affected by cognitive difficulties that preclude to the program's
             participation;

          -  ii) to be already undergoing rehabilitation before the entrance in the Transplantation
             Stem Cell Unit (TSCU).
